[White "The Euwe defense"]
[Black "?"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "02 The Blackmar Diemer"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "a-beginners-blitz-repertoire/course/7832, variation/317840"]

1. d4 d5 2. e4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. f3 exf3 5. Nxf3 e6 {The Euwe defence, as once 
recommended by Joe Gallagher. I used to play this myself - and I used to 
suffer!} 6. Bg5 Be7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Qe2 {As often happens, White can play OO - but 
we are emphasising the even more hacky OOO lines in this rep.} Nc6 9. O-O-O {We 
are hoping he will take our d pawn: Nxd4 Nxd4 Qxd4 Bxh7+ wins the Black queen!} 
Nb4 {Getting rid of our dangerous bishop on d3 looks like a more sensible idea 
for Black.} 10. Rhe1 Nxd3+ 11. Qxd3 c6 {If instead ...c5!? we push on with 12 
d5, and 12...Nxd5 loses to Bxe7!} 12. h4 {White threatens to take on f6 followed 
by g4 - g5.} *

