[SourceTitle "02 The Blackmar Diemer"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "a-beginners-blitz-repertoire/course/7832, variation/317848"]

1. d4 d5 2. e4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. f3 exf3 5. Nxf3 c6 {This is probably the best 
defence to the BDG. The main line against it involves Bc4, Ne5 and either g4 or 
OO; I am going to recommend something slightly unusual.} 6. Bc4 Bf5 {Bg4?? falls 
into a trap - White can answer it with Ne5!?, and if BxQ then Bxf7 is an amusing 
mate. wd66 points out the better defense: Bg4?? Ne5 Be6!, when Bxe6 fe OO is 
still really good for White, but his Bxf7+ wins our pawn back and leaves Black 
worse in terms of structure, king safety and development. Objectively Bxf7+ is a 
little better, but snap mates are fun, so I'd suggest Bxf7+ for blitz and Ne5 
for bullet:)} 7. Bg5 e6 8. Nh4 Bg6 9. Nxg6 hxg6 10. Qd3 {White intends h4 and 
OOO. Black's position is tricky to play in practice, and he has to watch out for 
a sacrifice on e6, followed up by Qxg6.} *

