1. d4 d5 2. e4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. f3 exf3 5. Nxf3 Bf5 {This is a less accurate 
way of trying to get the ...c6, ...Bf5 line. But White has to know the correct 
plan- Ne5 followed by g4.} 6. Ne5 e6 7. g4 Bg6 8. Bg2 c6 9. h4 {And we are back 
in our line against the Teichmann} ({5...Bg4}) {defense.} *

