1. d4 d5 2. e4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. f3 Bf5 {Not a silly move, and gets played 
sometimes.} 5. fxe4 {If you are feeling adventurous, you could try 5 g4!} Nxe4 
6. Qf3 Nxc3 {Nd6 can be met by Bf4 followed by OOO} 7. bxc3 Qc8 8. Rb1 c6 9. Nh3 
e6 10. Bd3 {This time we do go short. Black still has an extra pawn, but White 
is very active.} Be7 11. O-O O-O 12. Bxf5 exf5 13. Bd2 *

[Event "A beginner's blitz repertoire"]
