[SourceTitle "02 The Blackmar Diemer"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "a-beginners-blitz-repertoire/course/7832, variation/317854"]

1. d4 d5 2. e4 e6 {Black has transposed to a main line king pawn opening. The 
objectively best moves for White now are either Nc3 or Nd2. But we have a tricky 
alternative available which is much more in the style of our other lines.} 3. 
Be3 dxe4 {If Nf6 then e5 is probably best, but Nd2 is most in keeping with the 
rep.} 4. Nd2 Nf6 {If f5, then f3 is probably better for us than the main line.} 
5. f3 exf3 6. Ngxf3 Be7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Qe2 {White can castle either way. OOO 
looks most all in...} Nbd7 9. O-O-O {Objectively, White's position is dubious. 
But in a practical game - particularly blitz - White has a lot of attacking 
chances, for instance with h4 followed by something to g5. There are of course 
reasons that this is not a main line against the French. For people looking for 
something a little sounder, but still hacky, I recommend looking into the Milner 
Barry (e4 e6 d4 d5 e5 c5 c3 Nc6 Nf3 Qb6 Bd3)} *

