1. d4 d5 2. e4 c6 {Black has done it again! This time we have a Caro Kann.} 3. 
f3 {Actually a fairly respectable move here. It is also the best scoring at this 
level, and given our repertoire, no surprise at all! To keep things simple, will 
only give a sample line.} dxe4 {If instead 3...e6 then White develops by Nc3, 
Bf4 and Qd3.} 4. fxe4 e5 5. Nf3 {Don't forget to stop Qh4+!} exd4 6. Bc4 Be6 7. 
Bxe6 fxe6 8. O-O Be7 9. Nxd4 Nf6 10. e5 Bc5 11. c3 Nd5 12. Qh5+ g6 13. Qg4 
{Black's position is simply atrocious.} *

