1. d4 Nf6 {With this move order, Black has an annoying defence against our 
line.} 2. Nc3 d5 3. e4 Nxe4 4. Nxe4 dxe4 5. Bc4 Bf5 6. g4 Bg6 7. Ne2 e5 {A much 
more active treatment} 8. Be3 Nd7 9. h4 h5 10. Ng3 hxg4 11. h5 Bh7 12. Qxg4 Nf6 
13. Qg5 {White is active. Black's best now is probably to offer a trade of 
queens with Nd7, after which White can repeat with Qg4 (coward!) or play on with 
O-O-O.} *

