really well...} 2. e4 fxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Nc6 {Much better than d5, but White 
still has some fun.} 5. d5 Ne5 6. Qe2 Nf7 7. Bxf6 exf6 8. Nxe4 Be7 9. d6 cxd6 
10. O-O-O O-O 11. Nc3 {Controlling d5. Plan is now some combination of moving 
the queen, bishop to d3 or c4, f4 (to control e5) and Nf3.} *

